Super easy to make! Made a few changes just because I had ingredients lying around needing to be used. I added white chocolate and Greek yoghurt to the Panna Cotta, which really made it whole lot better. I also used Gelatin leaves instead of powder, no water was added, and the mixture was really smooth & creamy. The compote I used frozen berries, added a splash of peach schnapps, cranberry juice, water and rose essence with cinnamon sugar. The compote kept getting so much compliments!

