I made this again tonight as I still had some berries left over. I didn't have all the whipping cream I needed, so I used some 1/2 and 1/2 and cut the gelatin by 1/2 tsp. Still great, lighter, and less firm, which I like. If you use the whole amount the texture is like jello.

Rating: 4
Got rave reviews from my Italian friends for a dinner party. I would cut the gelatin by a 1/2 tsp and only use 2 as it was a little firm for my liking, but otherwise, great flavor and sooooo easy for such an elegant presentation. I used a bag of frozen mixed berries, put them in a bowl with the sugar when I made the pudding and they were perfectly macerated and ready by the time I served it. I did half with the moscato and 1/2 without, both were great. Will definitely make again, this is a forever keeper!

